--- !u!114 &1114608296
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1114608292}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 815257741d05b2742807c2d867806aa3, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PopupTrigger
  message: '<size=15><b>LOG-001</b> // Cycle 04 // Year 312 A.E. // Author: U-067



    <b>Departure
    from Station Aurelius</b>



    Departure confirmed. Aurelius Station shrinks
    behind me now a rusted ring of light slowly swallowed by the dark.



    Hard
    to believe that hunk of metal is home. Half the docking bays are sealed off.
    Each sector''s life support has been running on borrowed time for months. I could
    hear the hull groaning when I walked the corridor to my ship for the last time.



    The
    commander gave the briefing. Didn''t sugarcoat it. Reserves down to <b>14 months</b>.
    Recycler efficiency dropping. Three stations have gone dark in the last year
    with no signals, no survivors recovered.



    They''re calling volunteers <i>"candidates."</i>
    Sounds better than what we are.



    My unit designation ran pre-flight diagnostics
    while I stowed my kit. It flagged two minor hull micro-fractures from the last
    supply run. Already patched before I finished my coffee.



    I don''t know
    what''s out there. Nobody does anymore.



    But there has to be something.



    <i><b>***END
    OF LOG***</b></i></size>'
  popupPrompt: {fileID: 1302333700}
  popupText: {fileID: 176548432}
  lightanimation: {fileID: 0}
  triggerSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 4657c39144d5d8742a6da7fc7d387011, type: 3}
  audioSource: {fileID: 5459866632775208871}
  volume: 1
