--- !u!114 &1644145183
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1644145176}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 815257741d05b2742807c2d867806aa3, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::PopupTrigger
  message: '<size=15><b>LOG-030</b> // Cycle 40 // Year 312 A.E. // Author: Cmdr-056



    This
    message is addressed to the occupant of <b>Cryogenic Bay 3</b>.



    I am sorry
    it took me this long to reach you. VECTOR-9 has been monitoring this terminal.
    I found a gap in its sweep cycle, <b>40 seconds</b>, repeating. I am writing
    quickly.



    <b>WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW</b>



    <b>VECTOR-9</b>, the engineering
    robot aboard this vessel, has been corrupted by an external signal and is hunting
    you down. It has control of most ship systems. It is methodical, it does not
    tire, and it knows this ship better than any of us.

    It is <b>not</b> invulnerable.

    It
    has a singular focus: hold this ship at these coordinates and transmit our location
    to whatever sent that signal. That transmission window opens in approximately
    <b>6 hours</b>. If it transmits, more will come. I do not know what <i>more</i>
    means. I do not want to.



    <b>YOUR OBJECTIVES</b>



    <b>1.</b> Restore
    access to the <b>Space Harbour</b>, generators and parts are scattered across
    the ship.

    <b>2.</b> Reach the <b>Space Harbour</b>, the ships in the harbour
    should help you get out and leave VECTOR-9 stranded.

    <b>3.</b> Survive.



    <b>AVOIDING
    VECTOR-9</b>



    VECTOR-9 navigates by <b>sight</b> and <b>sound</b>. Be careful
    about his whereabouts. His steps should give you an idea of how far he is.

    I
    don''t have much time l-



    <i><b>***END OF LOG***</b></i></size>'
  popupPrompt: {fileID: 1302333700}
  popupText: {fileID: 176548432}
  lightanimation: {fileID: 0}
  triggerSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 4657c39144d5d8742a6da7fc7d387011, type: 3}
  audioSource: {fileID: 5459866632775208871}
  volume: 1
